Class PlayerMap<V>

          net.amoebaman.utils.maps.PlayerMap<V>
Type Parameters:

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,V>
public class PlayerMap<V>
extends java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,V>

A class that attempts to overcome the traditional aversion to using org.bukkit.entity.Player as the key type for a Map, namely that Player references can be quite large and we don't want to keep them around after they're gone unless necessary.

This class is externally typed with Player as the key type, but internally uses String as the key type, using the player's name.

In addition to this memory-saving measure, this map also allows the contents to be accessed through either the player's name or the player object itself, meaning no more hassle with HumanEntity.getName() or Bukkit.getPlayer(String) when you want to pull out of a map.

If all this wasn't enough, you can also specify a default value when the map is initialized that will be returned instead of null if the key you're looking for doesn't exist within the map.

Author:
AmoebaMan
